Seven bomb blasts hit Jaipur, killing 80 and injuring 200 in a terror attack with foreign connections.
Pakistan was not directly accused.
Previous attacks in Hyderabad and Punjab left many dead.
Global leaders, including the US and UK, condemned the violence.
France offered support to India in fighting terrorism.
The blasts targeted markets and temples, sparking fears of Hindu-Muslim tensions.
Authorities blamed Pakistan-based groups for the attacks.
The US stood with India against terrorism.
The death toll rose to over 60, with many injured.
High alert was issued nationwide to prevent further attacks.
